## Devnet Swap Guide

## Install Dependencies (Ubuntu)
```
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y g++ libssl-dev make cmake pkg-config curl
```

## Clone and Update WebCLI
```
git clone https://github.com/octra-labs/webcli.git
cd webcli
git pull
```

## Build WebCLI
```
chmod +x setup.sh
./setup.sh
```
This compiles octra_wallet and required libraries

## Add Your Nano Wallet
```
nano wallet.json
```
Paste your wallet details:
```
{
  "priv": "YOUR_BASE64_PRIVATE_KEY",
  "addr": "YOUR_OCT_ADDRESS",
  "rpc": "http://165.227.225.79:8080"
}
```

Save the file:
Press Ctrl + X
Press Y
Press Enter

## Start the Wallet Server
```
./octra_wallet
```
This launches the local server on port 8420

## Open the Swap Interface
```
http://127.0.0.1:8420/swap.html
```

You’re Ready

If your wallet is detected and funded with devnet OCT, you can now:

Swap OCT ↔ tUSD

Interact with the deployed SWAP contract
